Description:

🎯 Full Homoglyph Punycode Viewer

This Python script allows you to explore all possible homoglyphs (look-alike characters) for letters, numbers, and some symbols, and instantly converts them into Punycode.
It’s perfect for:

Phishing awareness and testing

Domain security research

Unicode and IDN exploration

Features:

Interactive terminal interface with rich colored tables

Supports letters a-z, numbers 0-9, and symbols like @, ., -

Shows all possible homoglyphs for each character

Displays the Punycode equivalent of each variant

Easy to use — just type a character and see results instantly.


Example usage:

$ python3 punycode-homoglyph-viewer.py
Enter a letter, number, or symbol: a

🔎 Punycode Variants for 'a'
